00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.000
So my talk is on extending Quarto, and we do that with Quarto extensions, and I just

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:21.760
want to say, Quarto really does a lot, like, when I first saw it, I was, it was unbelievable

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:28.680
that it could do articles, websites, blogs, books, presentations, and even knowledge repos.

00:00:29.680 --> 00:00:32.680
That is a lot in and of itself.

00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:38.680
But also, you can make products that contain computations performed with Python, R, Julia,

00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:44.680
Observable, and that's a lot more, that's just quite a comprehensive package that Quarto

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:45.680
delivers.

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:49.680
And now we have extensions, or we had extensions for quite a while, and they really can open

00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:52.680
up a whole world of customization possibilities.

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:55.680
And there's lots of them.

00:00:55.680 --> 00:00:58.680
I was really impressed that there's so many Quarto extensions.

00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:03.680
They can barely fit in this slide here, and that's only just a small, you know, portion

00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:04.680
of them.

00:01:04.680 --> 00:01:05.680
So there's lots.

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.680
There's definitely people chomping at the bit to create extensions for Quarto, which

00:01:09.680 --> 00:01:11.680
is really impressive.

00:01:12.680 --> 00:01:15.680
Okay, so a big question is, we know there's lots of extensions.

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:17.680
Where can you find these extensions?

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:20.680
Where's the best place to sort of get introduced to them?

00:01:20.680 --> 00:01:25.680
Okay, the place I like to go, always, is the Quarto.org website.

00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:29.680
Okay, it's a great starting point for lots, you know, of Quarto things.

00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:33.680
And really, the section you want to go to is in the top nav, Extensions, which is just

00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:36.680
a huge section in and of itself.

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:41.680
So in there, you'll find just like, you know, just the extensions themselves.

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:46.680
They're broken down by the type, and there's like a Creating Extensions section, which

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:50.680
is also really comprehensive and huge.

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:54.680
Pretty much everything you need to like learn about extensions in Quarto and to be a user

00:01:54.680 --> 00:01:57.680
or a creator of extensions is all in there.

00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:02.680
Okay, I'm just going to like break down the four different types of extensions in case

00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:05.680
you've never heard of them or you just want a little more explanation.

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:11.679
So the types of extensions are shortcode slash filter extensions.

00:02:11.679 --> 00:02:16.679
So with those, you modify select parts of a Quarto document, and shortcodes are a little

00:02:16.679 --> 00:02:17.679
bit different than filters.

00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:18.679
Shortcodes have a little syntax.

00:02:18.679 --> 00:02:20.679
I'll get into that a little bit more later.

00:02:20.679 --> 00:02:27.679
And filters just sort of automatically transform sections of your document.

00:02:27.679 --> 00:02:31.679
If you're writing an article for a journal, you'll be happy to know that there's a whole

00:02:31.679 --> 00:02:35.679
world of journal article extensions, which is great.

00:02:35.679 --> 00:02:38.679
There's a large amount, and it's growing every day.

00:02:38.679 --> 00:02:44.679
This is sort of similar in spirit to the articles package in R, except this is all

00:02:44.679 --> 00:02:45.679
in Quarto.

00:02:45.679 --> 00:02:49.679
Custom formats, we saw before that there's already lots of formats.

00:02:49.679 --> 00:02:52.679
You can create your own format, which is quite amazing.

00:02:52.679 --> 00:02:57.679
So with extensions, you can write your own to create a custom format, which is just unbelievable

00:02:57.679 --> 00:02:58.679
to me.

00:02:58.679 --> 00:03:05.679
Reveal.js, if you're using Reveal.js to create a presentation, it's great.

00:03:05.679 --> 00:03:09.679
There's extensions that create themes for these presentations.

00:03:09.679 --> 00:03:12.679
It's a really wonderful section of the site.

